@startuml
title Use Case 4: Sending a Message

actor Sender as "User (Sender)"
actor Recipient as "User (Recipient)"
boundary GUI as "Client GUI"
control Client as "Client App"
control Server as "Server"
collections Cache as "Server Cache\n(Users + Conversation headers)"
collections Store as "Server Persistent Storage\n(Messages)"

== Compose and send ==
Sender -> GUI: Type message\nClick "Send"
GUI -> Client: SendMessage(conversationId,\n messageText, attachments/meta)

Client -> Server: PostMessage(conversationId,\n messagePayload, sessionToken)

== Server processing ==
Server -> Store: Append message to conversation
Store --> Server: Stored (messageId, timestamp)

Server -> Cache: Lookup conversation participants
Cache --> Server: Participant list + online status

== Delivery to online recipients ==
loop For each logged-in recipient
  Server --> Client: PushMessage(conversationId,\n messageId, messagePayload)
  Client -> GUI: Display new message
end
@enduml
